<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.1.15_0001" />
<note type="curatorial">Davis Coll. NY Pub Lib 9</note>
<fw type="curatorial">15</fw>

<opener>
<salute>My dear Davis:&#8212;</salute>
</opener>
	<p>I am anxiously awaiting the
arrival of the <hi rend="underline">profile</hi> taken in the 
<hi rend="underline">blue coat</hi>. The picture taken
in the black one is rather vague.
All that I gather from it is that
you are taller or shorter than
the other gentleman who is not
you. I am very thankful for this,
however.</p>
	<p>I wonder if Mr. Waters has 
given you a headache.</p>
	<p>I'm glad you have lots of fun,
even tho' I have less. Your
unfailing optimism must be a 
great comfort to you. As for me,
altho' I fight against them, the 
blue devils do come at times
	Don't forget the profile&#8212;Please.</p>
<closer>
	<salute>Yours sincerely,</salute>
	<signed>Jno. G. Neihardt</signed>
<dateline>Bancroft, Nebr, <date>Apr. 20, 1906</date></dateline>
</closer>
</div1>
